<subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-division-of-whole-numbers">
  <title>Division of whole numbers</title>
  <sidebyside>
  <p> 
    Sarah has 24 apples and wants to share them equally among <m>6</m> friends. To find out how many apples each friend gets, she divides <m>24 รท 6 = 4</m>. This means each friend receives <m>4</m> apples. Therefore, Sarah applies division to share the apples equally. 
  </p>
  <image source="/apples.png">
    <shortdescription></shortdescription>
  </image>
  </sidebyside>
  <activity>
    <statement>
      <p>
        
      </p>
      <p>
        1. Gather 30 books at the front of the classroom and form <m>5</m> groups.
      </p>
      <p>
        2. In groups, discuss the number of books each group will get.
      </p>
      <p>
        3. In turns, one student from each group to collect and place the book in their group tables untill there are no books left.
      </p>
      <p>
        4. Each group to count the number of books they have. Did each group receive the same number of books? Was there a remainder?
      </p>
      <p>
        5. Gather all books again and add <m>7</m> more then count them if it amounts to <m>37</m>.
      </p>
      <p>
        6. In the same groups, follow the steps you used to divide <m>30</m> books to identify how many books each group will get. 
      </p>
      <p>
        7. Discuss if all books were equally distributed.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </activity>
